Key Match Events: Haris Rauf and Hasan Ali led Pakistan's pace attack to stop Netherlands at the score 205.
Bas de Leede scored the highest 67 runs while Vikramjit Singh smashed 52 runs for Netherlands.
Hasan Ali took the first wicket as he dismissed Max O'Dowd.
Colin Ackermann was dismissed by spinner Iftikhar Ahmed.
Bas de Leede bowled a wonderful spell to restrict Pakistan innings to 286 runs.
Mohammad Rizwan and Saud Shakeel played in a wonderful partnership to pull back Pakistan from a low-scoring end.
Bas de Leede dismissed Mohammad Rizwan, Iftikhar Ahmed, Shadab Khan, and Hasan Ali.
Haris Rauf successfully grabbed the last wicket.
Logan van Beek smashed a massive SIX against Shadab Khan.
Mohammad Nawaz grabbed a big wicket as Bas de Leede walked back to the pavilion.
Haris Rauf clinched the wicket of Teja Nidamanuru.
Iftikhar Ahmed dismissed Colin Ackermann on his first ball.
